<HEADLINE>
MANNING PICKS OLE MISS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOHN MILLER 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ For the second time this week, Texas missed
out on one of the top quarterback prospects in the nation.
</P>
<P>
   Eli Manning of Newman High School in New Orleans committed to
Mississippi, his mother, Olivia Manning, said yesterday. He chose
the Rebels over Texas and Virginia.
</P>
<P>
   Manning, a member of the ``Star-Telegram'''s National Top 100
recruits, is the son of former NFL quarterback Archie Manning and
the brother of Peyton Manning, the starting quarterback for the
Indianapolis Colts. Archie Manning played quarterback for
Mississippi before going to the NFL.
</P>
<P>
   On Tuesday, Chris Simms, the son of former NFL quarterback and
current TV analyst Phil Simms, committed to Tennessee. Simms, also
a member of the ``Star-Telegram'''s National Top 100 recruits,
chose the Volunteers over Penn State and Texas.
</P>
<P>
   The Longhorns have a commitment from Westlake quarterback Adam
Hall, a member of the ``Star-Telegram'''s State Top 100 recruits.
VOLS GET TOP LINEBACKER Austin McCallum linebacker Devon Davis
committed to Tennessee, his mother, Ruby Davis, said.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's loved Tennessee for a long time,'' Ruby Davis said. ``He
was honored that all the other schools were interested in him.
Tennessee just seemed to be the right place for him.''
</P>
<P>
   Davis, a member of the ``Star-Telegram'''s State Top 100
recruits, had been to Michigan and had official visits set up for
Texas A&AMP;M and UCLA. His mother said she does not believe Davis will
take those visits. BELL KICKER PICKS AIR FORCE L.D. Bell kicker
Adam Thornton has received his appointment to the Air Force Academy
and has committed to the Falcons.
</P>
<P>
   ``Basically, I want to fly, and Air Force has the premier
planes,'' Thornton said. ``I want to get into their astronaut
program.''
</P>
<P>
   Thornton made 9 of 15 field-goal attempts this season, including
four longer than 40 yards and made all 18 of his extra-point tries.
He also averaged 38.6 yards per punt for the Blue Raiders this
season. He had considered Navy, Washington and Washington State.
SYRACUSE LANDS GARLAND LINEMAN Garland offensive lineman Tre Mathis
committed to Syracuse yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   ``The first thing I saw when I got there was the closeness and
the unity of the players,'' Mathis said. ``I felt at home as soon
as I got there. The players really welcomed me and I fit in with
the crowd.''
</P>
<P>
   Mathis, 6-foot-3, 340 pounds and a member of the
``Star-Telegram'''s State Top 100 recruits, had also seriously
considered Arkansas, but the Razorbacks withdrew their scholarship
offer, making the decision easy for Mathis.
</P>
<P>
   Mathis picked Syracuse over Oklahoma State and Tennessee. He has
an official visit with Tennessee on Jan. 15 and said he was unsure
if he is going to take it or not. BUFFS GET HOUSTON TE Houston
Forest Brook tight end Terry Phillips has committed to Colorado. He
will still take a visit to TCU on Jan. 15, but has canceled his
official visit to Texas A&AMP;M.
</P>
</TEXT>
