<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-NOTEBOOK-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SANDERS LIKELY TO MISS GAME WITH EAGLES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Cowboys coach Chan Gailey all but ruled Deion
Sanders out of tomorrow's crucial matchup with the Philadelphia
Eagles after the cornerback was unable to practice for a second
consecutive day.
</P>
<P>
   Sanders, who has been sidelined the past four-and-a-half games
with a sprained left toe, will be re-evaluated again today and
before the game, but Gailey said ``he's very doubtful at this
point.''
</P>
<P>
   ``We'll see how it goes, but that's where it stands right now,''
Gailey said.
</P>
<P>
   Kevin Smith will start at right cornerback in place of Sanders.
Kevin Mathis will start at left cornerback.
</P>
<P>
   Gailey acknowledged that Sanders' absence would be a setback,
considering that the Pro Bowl-bound cornerback/kick returner badly
wanted to play, and the team sorely missed his big-play ability.
The Cowboys are 0-6 the past two years when Sanders is not in the
starting lineup.
</P>
<P>
   Now, there is a question as to whether Sanders will play in the
regular-season finale against the Washington Redskins on Dec. 27.
If the Cowboys beat the Eagles and clinch the NFC East title,
Sanders could be held out until the playoffs, which begin on Jan.
2. BACK RUNNING Gailey said he can't put a finger on why the
offense has had problems the past two weeks, but he has some ideas
about the running game.
</P>
<P>
   Gailey blames himself for giving up on the run too quickly and
links his thought process to his infatuation with quarterback Troy
Aikman's record-setting 455-yard passing performance against the
Minnesota Vikings.
</P>
<P>
   He doesn't blame running back Emmitt Smith, who has totaled 48
yards the past two weeks combined after rushing for just 44 against
the Vikings on Thanksgiving Day.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't think there was any place for Emmitt to run,'' Gailey
said. ``And I have found myself getting away from the running game
\Rwhen they have fallen behind\S.''
</P>
<P>
   Gailey said he will make a more concerted effort to stay
committed to the run against the Eagles, as offense is best when it
is balanced. BRIEFLY Tight end David LaFleur (sprained knee) will
not play against the Eagles. ... Wide receiver Michael Irvin
(strained lower back) looked good in practice yesterday, and Gailey
doesn't expect him to have any limitations against the Eagles.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
