<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, Dec. 20, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Stew Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-COOLING (Los Angeles) _ With the fast-track installation
of air conditioning stalled in court, some Los Angeles Unified
School District officials said they are pushing to hire individual
contractors to do the work _ a practice that previously caused
problems with quality and cost overruns. By David R. Baker. (Will
move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   LEUKEMIA-SURVIVOR (Los Angeles) _ Seven-year-old Amador Navarro
and his family will celebrate his recovery from leukemia by hosting
a bone marrow drive at their parish, the Santa Rosa Church in San
Fernando. By Yvette Cabrera. (Will move in the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   SOOTHING-HOSPITAL (Los Angeles) _ Saltwater aquariums with
beautiful fish, gurgling water fountains, soft classical music, and
whatever aromas you want to fill your nostrils to help take your
mind a thousand miles away from your pain. It's the transitional
care unit at Sherman Oaks Hospital and Health Center, where
patients are recovering from surgeries, hip replacements,
pneumonia, respiratory problems _ you name it. By Dennis McCarthy.
(Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
