stories for Sunday. If you have questions, please call at
202-298-6920.    (The ``HNS'' tag appears in all sluglines.)   
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLINTON-IMPEACH (Washington) _ Following a divisive day of
debate, the House of Representatives votes on impeachment for only
the second time in American history. By JOHN C. HENRY.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-REAX (Washington) _ President Clinton, vowing to fight
rather than resign, stages a rally of Democrats at the White House
following the historic House vote that sets the stage for a Senate
trial on his removal. By STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
