   IMPEACH-ANALYSIS (Washington) _ The last time the House
impeached a president, it was an indirect result of the Civil War.
This time it came as the indirect result of cultural wars. In many
ways the House vote was the 1960s come home to roost: Clinton, a
classic baby boomer, vs. the direct descendants of Barry
Goldwater's ``extremism in the defense of liberty is no vice.'' By
CRAGG HINES.
