   INTERRACE _ Interracial marriage, banned by the Alabama
constitution but rendered moot by U.S. Supreme Court rulings, will
draw scrutiny during the upcoming session of the state Legislature.
A Montgomery lawmaker says he'll draft a bill to kill the statute,
and the majority of those who participated in a recent survey
favored dumping the archiac legislation. But at least one state
representative says he's still opposed to interracial marriages. In
South Carolina in November, voters decided to erase a similar ban
from their state constitution. (Manuel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
