regarded as a great leader of the NBA players' union. He united the
players in the Latrell Sprewell matter, and has tried to keep them
focused during the lockout. But like Stern, the hit in the wallet
is starting to erode his popularity. By Howard Beck. (Will move in
the ``n'' California, ``a'' national and ``s'' sports news files.)
