guard for some 240 crosses placed by Catholic zealots over the last
five months at Auschwitz. A former member of Poland's Solidarity
Union, Switon arrived at the camp, took up residence in a tent, and
declared that he had to defend Polish soil against the Jews. ``The
Jewish people want to have power in Poland,'' he says. ``But these
Christian symbols show we will not bow to their blackmail.'' (Roger
