BKN-STERN (Los Angeles) _ The NBA was thriving, and David Stern was
one of the people being given the credit. The lucrative TV
contracts were lining the owners' pockets. Everything was wonderful
until the owners decided that they were giving away too much of the
pie. 
By Howard Beck. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BKN-HUNTER (Los Angeles) _ Like David Stern, Billy Hunter is
regarded as a great leader of the NBA players' union. He united the
players in the Latrell Sprewell matter, and has tried to keep them
focused during the lockout. But like Stern, the hit in the wallet
is starting to erode his popularity. 
By Howard Beck. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
