r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-COWBOYS-EAGLES-TE     12-19 0979
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-EAGLES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS FACE SEASON'S DEFINING MOMENTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
``''December is the month that defines the teams that are going to
go on and have success in the playoffs. I think if you are going to
have success in the playoffs, you need to play well in
December.'''' _ Cowboys quarterback Troy Aikman on Nov. 30
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Cowboys quarterback Troy Aikman's pre-December
soliloquy has begot cornerback Deion Sanders' pre-Christmas
reality.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't believe in getting to the playoffs and being able to
turn it on,'' said Sanders, sounding more like the Grinch than Kris
Kringle.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have to build up to that point. Right now, we are built up
to level of coming right back home in the first round. That's the
way we are playing right now.''
</P>
<P>
   A three-game losing streak _ built on losses the past two weeks
to New Orleans and Kansas City and the Thanksgiving Day setback to
Minnesota _ has redefined the Cowboys (8-6) as more first-round
playoff fodder than the Super Bowl contenders they seemed to be a
month ago.
</P>
<P>
   Now they face what many Cowboys players are calling a must-win
game against the Philadelphia Eagles (3-11) today to finally clinch
the NFC East. More important, a victory could begin the process of
changing the Cowboys' December definition.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys clinched a playoff berth yesterday when Tampa Bay
lost to Washington, 20-16. However, the team's focus isn't on just
qualifying for the playoffs, but on making a lengthy playoff run.
</P>
<P>
   With that in mind, Cowboys owner Jerry Jones is calling today's
game as ``big a game as we've had at Texas Stadium in the past two
years.'' He expresses confidence his struggling team can turn it
around.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not concerned with just getting to the playoffs,'' Jones
said. ``I'm about playing well against the Eagles and playing well
when we get to the playoffs. And we are running out of time to get
to point where we are playing well enough to make a long run in the
playoffs.''
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys will clinch the NFC East title for the sixth time in
the past seven seasons with a victory today. Or they could back
into the division title with a loss by the second-place Arizona
Cardinals in one of their final two games.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've got to do it \Rtoday\S,'' Cowboys receiver Michael Irvin
said. ``Right now we have to concentrate on losing this first deal.
That's the reality of it all. The last thing we want to do is go
into the last game of the season saying we need to win this game to
get where we want to go. We don't want to put ourselves in that
position.''
</P>
<P>
   Despite Aikman's pre-December statement, history shows the
Cowboys can have success in the playoffs without steamrolling teams
before Christmas.
</P>
<P>
   In 1994, the Cowboys were 2-2 in December, including a 1-2 mark
in their last three games. However, they made it to the NFC title
game. In 1995, the Cowboys won the Super Bowl after going 2-2 in
December.
</P>
<P>
   But, in contrast, the Cowboys were 2-1 in December in 1996 _
with the loss in a give-up season finale in which they sat out most
of the starters to get ready for the playoffs. But they lost in the
divisional round to Carolina.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman, who called the past few weeks painful, used this history
lesson to revise his position.
</P>
<P>
   ``The season is not lost by any means,'' Aikman said. ``If we go
out and win \Rtoday\S, we are right back where we want to be. We
win the East. We are in the playoffs. And anything can happen.''
</P>
<P>
   Though confident the Cowboys still have reason for hope, Aikman
agrees the faith will ring hollow if the Cowboys don't make a
marked improvement in their play of late _ which has included a
paltry running game, an inability to make a big play in the passing
game, a porous run defense and a nonexistent pass rush.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys coach Chan Gailey has said he is shocked by the recent
difficulties, especially on offense. Running back Emmitt Smith, who
has rushed for 44, 6 and 42 yards in the past three games,
respectively, said the problems blindsided him as well.
</P>
<P>
   Irvin, also at a loss for explanation, is taking solace in the
team's experience of playing tough games _ saying that ``just like
it turned bad, we can flip it and make it happen the other way.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we will be fine,'' he continued. ``I'm confident we
will have that sense of urgency. It's that Custer thing, the last
stand. Either you stand or sit for a while. But right now, we've
got to get there and win this one game first.''
</P>
<P>
   Making the stakes more ``acute'' against the Eagles, Jones said,
are the questions surrounding the status of Sanders, whose absence
the past three games with a sprained left big toe is considered a
reason for the Cowboys' problems. If they clinch the title against
the Eagles, the Cowboys likely will hold Sanders out of the season
finale against Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Having Sanders healthy for the playoffs is partly why Jones is
confident the recent slide has not totally defined his team's
postseason chances.
</P>
<P>
   Sanders, who is doubtful for the Eagles game, said he is getting
frustrated with ``sitting on the sideline watching us play and
losing games.'' The Cowboys are 0-6 the past two seasons without
Sanders in the starting lineup.
</P>
<P>
   However, Sanders refused to view himself as the savior and said
the Cowboys must not only win the next two games but look good
doing it.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not going to blame it on the absence of a few players. We
are playing terrible football right now,'' Sanders said. ``It will
help to get some guys back. But we are playing terrible football.
We need to play better. Anything is possible in the playoffs, but
these next two games are important in according to how you are
going to compete in the playoffs.''
</P>
<P>
   And to how the Cowboys will be ultimately defined _ or
redefined.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
