to play red light-green light, a child's game where players run
when the leader shouts, ``Green light!'' and stop at the call of
``Red light!'' But they ran when she called ``Red light!'' and
stopped for the green. Smith was perplexed by their confused faces
until she realized that the girls had never seen a traffic light.
But, for the first time, there is a Brownie Troop in Aguila. By
KARINA BLAND. Move in `A` category.
