<HEADLINE>
LAYOFF FRUSTRATES HACKETT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC coach Paul Hackett's frustration continued
Saturday over the Trojans' lackluster practice after their week
off.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've got a long ways to go,'' Hackett said. ``We are a
distracted team. We're a different football team compared to the
team that beat Notre Dame.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett blamed the layoff, the length of the season and finals
as the reasons the Trojans are far from being mentally or
physically ready for the Dec.31 Sun Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   ``This team has never done this before,'' he said. ``There's no
crispness. No tempo.''
</P>
<P>
   USC has not played in a postseason game since the 1996 Rose
Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Hackett compared USC's Saturday practice to a spring workout.
USC will have today off, then Hackett intends to have the
first-string offense and defense play against each other to help
raise the level of intensity during practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, we're going to go for it,''
Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   The bowl schedule has also been an adjustment for Hackett, who
is used to the NFL season and was not accustomed to taking a finals
break, or trying to get a team back into shape after a brief
layoff.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a new thing you have to deal with in college,'' Hackett
said. ``It's wonderful going to a bowl, but do we get it done and
win the bowl game? That's what I'm finding out about and it's
discouraging.''
</P>
<P>
   Recruits on campus: Some big names continued their recruiting
visits Saturday. Those visiting include defensive lineman Ty Warren
of Bryan, Texas; offensive lineman Lenny Vandermade of Mater Dei;
tailback Onterrio Smith of Sacramento Grant; linebacker Chris
Prosser and lineman Regis Crawford of San Diego Morse; defensive
lineman George Heather of Hancock Junior College and kicker David
Newberry of Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Also visiting are four players who already have committed: wide
receiver Kareem Kelly of Long Beach Poly, linebacker Aaron Graham
of Bakersfield and defensive tackles Bernard Riley and Sagan
Atuatasi of Los Alamitos.
</P>
<P>
   Steinbacher commits: Offensive lineman Nate Steinbacher
(6-foot-6, 330 pounds) of Esperanza High in Anaheim gave USC an
oral commitment this weekend. He is the first offensive lineman to
commit and chose USC over Nebraska.
</P>
<P>
   Familiar staff: Former USC defensive line coach Jeff McInerney
has been named defensive coordinator at Nevada-Las Vegas, where he
will rejoin John Robinson. McInerney was defensive line coach at
Oregon State this past season. Ex-USC players DelVaughn Alexander
and Joe Barry are also on the UNLV coaching staff.
</P>
<P>
   Robinson hired former Texas offensive coordinator Gene Dahlquist
as his offensive coordinator. Former USC assistant John Jackson is
expected to be named running backs coach and associate head coach.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
